1
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:29,740
[Episode 29]

2
00:02:12,660 --> 00:02:14,096
Uncle Zhou?

3
00:02:15,420 --> 00:02:17,076
You finally caught up.

4
00:02:19,100 --> 00:02:21,300
What did he tell you?

5
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:22,840
The progress of the case.

6
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:24,673
I'll go see him tomorrow.

7
00:02:29,160 --> 00:02:31,196
The two of us will go see him.

8
00:02:34,379 --> 00:02:36,900
Wasn't it closed as an accident a while ago?

9
00:02:36,900 --> 00:02:38,440
Now there's new progress.

10
00:02:38,440 --> 00:02:41,220
They suspect it was arson
by a former Kuangxia employee.

11
00:02:41,220 --> 00:02:44,266
But they want to use it to bait Zhang Bin,
so they're keeping it quiet.

12
00:02:45,640 --> 00:02:46,670
Let's go.

13
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:50,030
Come back.

14
00:02:53,920 --> 00:02:55,059
What?

15
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:56,786
Nothing.

16
00:03:09,260 --> 00:03:10,386
Let's go.

17
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:25,966
Hurry up.

18
00:03:27,380 --> 00:03:28,600
Run faster.

19
00:03:33,539 --> 00:03:34,783
What?

20
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:38,110
What? Is the police here?

21
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:46,940
Keep an eye on him.

22
00:03:46,940 --> 00:03:48,093
How is it?

23
00:03:53,180 --> 00:03:54,199
They're coming.

24
00:03:54,199 --> 00:03:56,480
Where? Which way?

25
00:04:00,819 --> 00:04:02,219
They're not in plainclothes?

26
00:04:02,219 --> 00:04:03,845
I don't know.

27
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:11,969
If you hadn't been so impulsive,
we wouldn't be in this mess.

28
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:13,740
What did you say?

29
00:04:13,740 --> 00:04:15,266
Hu was just provoked.

30
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:18,900
If you ask me, Zhang Bin is a real scumbag.

31
00:04:18,900 --> 00:04:21,080
We're being chased like stray dogs.

32
00:04:21,080 --> 00:04:22,763
Yet he's doing just fine.

33
00:04:22,763 --> 00:04:27,540
Things have come to this,
and we can't go back to the site.

34
00:04:27,540 --> 00:04:29,340
What's the point of this nonsense?

35
00:04:29,340 --> 00:04:31,387
Think of a way out.

36
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:41,039
If Zhai were still here...

37
00:04:45,540 --> 00:04:46,640
Sit, sit.

38
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:48,176
Keep it low.

39
00:04:52,460 --> 00:04:55,600
Mr. Zhang heard that you and Manager Chen
had some misunderstandings.

40
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:58,838
You're all brothers. Why make things so ugly?

41
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:01,500
He still hasn't paid us back!

42
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:03,420
Who's his brother?

43
00:05:03,420 --> 00:05:04,780
What are you doing?

44
00:05:04,780 --> 00:05:06,676
I know things are tight for you all.

45
00:05:07,519 --> 00:05:11,040
Mr. Zhang doesn't intend to hold a grudge.

46
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:15,740
The original 160,000 yuan severance pay,
plus bank interest at three percent.

47
00:05:15,740 --> 00:05:18,012
Here is 180,000 yuan in cash.

48
00:05:22,580 --> 00:05:24,254
There's a catch, isn't there?

49
00:05:25,540 --> 00:05:27,340
Don't be like that.

50
00:05:27,340 --> 00:05:30,956
I just need you
to do one last favor for Mr. Zhang.

51
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:35,520
[Haoyun Logistics]

52
00:05:44,820 --> 00:05:45,959
Morning, Boss.

53
00:05:45,959 --> 00:05:47,640
- Morning, Ms. Miao.
- Morning.

54
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:10,740
[Records Room]

55
00:06:10,740 --> 00:06:12,215
Come in.

56
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:15,280
Hello. I'm from the audit team.

57
00:06:15,280 --> 00:06:18,400
I'm here
for the shipping department's contracts.

58
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:19,955
Let me check.

59
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:26,280
I don't see the approved request for the files.

60
00:06:26,280 --> 00:06:28,240
Our director has already submitted the request.

61
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:30,910
Maybe it's still in the middle of the process.

62
00:06:33,579 --> 00:06:35,100
Then we should wait for the approval.

63
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:37,520
The request hasn't reached me yet,
so I can't just give them to you.

64
00:06:37,520 --> 00:06:40,660
The team needs them urgently.
How about I take them now?

65
00:06:40,660 --> 00:06:43,002
I'll call my supervisor to ask about it.

66
00:06:44,259 --> 00:06:47,020
It's for the shipping department,
so Manager Chen should be in charge.

67
00:06:47,020 --> 00:06:48,602
You can call him.

68
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,460
<i>Hello, Manager Chen.</i>

69
00:06:58,460 --> 00:07:00,620
I have someone here from the audit team.
She's...

70
00:07:00,620 --> 00:07:01,699
Miao.

71
00:07:01,699 --> 00:07:03,260
Ms. Miao from the audit team.

72
00:07:03,260 --> 00:07:05,400
<i>She's asking for the shipping contracts.</i>

73
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:07,640
<i>Has the request been approved on your end?</i>

74
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:08,983
Hold on.

75
00:07:09,840 --> 00:07:11,920
<i>I see it. Everything looks fine.</i>

76
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:12,970
All right.

77
00:07:13,840 --> 00:07:15,266
Hold on.

78
00:07:49,340 --> 00:07:55,340
[Liu Bin Bo, Zhang Bin]
[Cargo Details]

79
00:07:55,340 --> 00:07:58,360
[All relevant personnel are bound
by confidentiality obligations]

80
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:06,800
[Cargo Details]

81
00:08:07,620 --> 00:08:08,620
[A New Message]

82
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:26,800
Jing.

83
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:29,011
Cen wants to see you in his office.

84
00:08:36,300 --> 00:08:37,562
Come in.

85
00:08:39,100 --> 00:08:40,434
Let's play a round.

86
00:08:57,960 --> 00:08:59,440
That's quite aggressive.

87
00:08:59,440 --> 00:09:01,340
Desperate times call for desperate measures.

88
00:09:01,340 --> 00:09:03,803
But you can't just ignore the consequences.

89
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:07,260
The Archives Department asked you, right?

90
00:09:07,260 --> 00:09:09,380
I found a way to fix the paperwork for you.

91
00:09:09,380 --> 00:09:12,560
But being this reckless isn't like you at all.

92
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:15,899
If I had told you beforehand,
you would've told me to be cautious.

93
00:09:15,899 --> 00:09:19,336
By acting first and reporting later,
you're forced to clean up my mess.

94
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:24,960
While it wasn't exactly proper,
it was certainly the most efficient way.

95
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:26,780
Violating protocol is a fact.

96
00:09:26,780 --> 00:09:28,890
But I had a reason for doing it.

97
00:09:29,799 --> 00:09:31,580
You have an answer for everything.

98
00:09:31,580 --> 00:09:33,320
I'll submit a violation report.

99
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:35,071
Deduct my pay as you see fit.

100
00:09:35,858 --> 00:09:39,255
I didn't call you here
just to hold you accountable.

101
00:09:40,319 --> 00:09:43,080
In their accounts,
there's been a hidden deficit.

102
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:48,020
But because the cash flow was decent,
for all these years, it went undetected.

103
00:09:48,020 --> 00:09:49,700
I looked at the raw data.

104
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:55,370
The shortfall dates back to the year
they turned a profit after Hongshen invested.

105
00:09:57,140 --> 00:09:58,980
But that's normal.

106
00:09:58,980 --> 00:10:01,060
Robbing Peter to pay Paul.

107
00:10:01,060 --> 00:10:03,520
High turnover can't be stopped.

108
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:05,980
But now Hongshen is going public.

109
00:10:05,980 --> 00:10:09,139
If something goes wrong with Haoyun
at this critical juncture,

110
00:10:09,139 --> 00:10:10,600
Hongshen will hold them accountable.

111
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:14,560
They might even cut their losses and pull out.

112
00:10:14,560 --> 00:10:17,181
Then Haoyun will surely be crippled.

113
00:10:18,700 --> 00:10:23,420
So, Zhang Bin will definitely find a way
to fill this hole.

114
00:10:23,420 --> 00:10:25,420
Kuangxia was Haoyun's predecessor.

115
00:10:25,420 --> 00:10:29,480
Zhang Bin got the funds
and built it to Haoyun's current scale.

116
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:32,460
Zhang Bin wanted to open up
a new transportation route.

117
00:10:32,460 --> 00:10:34,580
But this route isn't exactly clean.

118
00:10:34,580 --> 00:10:37,356
The police are already suspicious
and are watching closely.

119
00:10:38,413 --> 00:10:42,578
So, he can only take the risk
of shifting the blame.

120
00:10:44,599 --> 00:10:46,340
Therefore,

121
00:10:46,340 --> 00:10:51,500
even if the arsonist is found,
they won't find any connection to Haoyun.

122
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:52,679
Yes.

123
00:10:52,679 --> 00:10:54,659
There's no direct evidence yet.

124
00:10:54,659 --> 00:10:56,780
And since it involves a Lingang company,

125
00:10:56,780 --> 00:11:00,700
the police have no grounds
to issue a search warrant directly.

126
00:11:00,700 --> 00:11:04,179
Going through all that trouble
just to balance the books?

127
00:11:04,179 --> 00:11:05,636
I don't think so.

128
00:11:09,519 --> 00:11:13,262
It seems you already have a plan.

129
00:11:16,039 --> 00:11:18,523
The goods from Baiyou earlier,
which fleet were they from?

130
00:11:18,523 --> 00:11:19,900
Bai and Xu's.

131
00:11:19,900 --> 00:11:22,399
Bai drives the Lingang route,
handling small cargo.

132
00:11:22,399 --> 00:11:25,297
Xu handles the major retailers,
delivering nationwide.

133
00:11:27,279 --> 00:11:28,800
Where is Bai?

134
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:31,580
The schedule says he's driving today.

135
00:11:31,580 --> 00:11:34,101
Bai took the day off.
He asked me to fill in for him.

136
00:11:36,332 --> 00:11:39,397
Yes. Bai has been taking a lot of leave lately.
He's missed several shifts.

137
00:11:39,397 --> 00:11:41,960
Actually, lately, a few other veteran drivers
have also been missing shifts.

138
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:44,159
A few newcomers have joined us, though.

139
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:47,419
Several have been replaced.

140
00:11:47,419 --> 00:11:49,580
Bai isn't feeling well.
He'll be here this afternoon.

141
00:11:49,580 --> 00:11:51,687
I don't know about anything else.

142
00:11:54,300 --> 00:11:55,965
You're not driving this day.

143
00:11:55,965 --> 00:11:58,539
For small trucks like yours,
you've only made three trips, right?

144
00:11:58,539 --> 00:12:00,059
There's no other dispatch schedule?

145
00:12:00,059 --> 00:12:03,200
That's true.
That's how the company arranged it.

146
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:05,799
Oh, right. The drivers are free,
but the trucks aren't.

147
00:12:05,799 --> 00:12:08,620
Didn't Mr. Tao hire some new drivers recently?

148
00:12:08,620 --> 00:12:10,937
I guess it's their turn to drive.

149
00:12:14,019 --> 00:12:15,700
New drivers?

150
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:17,040
Yes.

151
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:22,060
[Liu]

152
00:12:38,680 --> 00:12:40,840
[Warehouse A2]

153
00:12:44,380 --> 00:12:49,766
I suspect the route Zhang wants to establish
is linked to smuggling.

154
00:12:53,059 --> 00:12:54,460
After the team leaves,

155
00:12:54,460 --> 00:12:58,147
I'll stay in Teng City under the pretext
of handling the follow-up work.

156
00:13:00,039 --> 00:13:02,600
Yi, here.

157
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:03,840
Try this.

158
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:06,460
I just brought this back from Lingang.

159
00:13:06,460 --> 00:13:08,653
You can't find it in Teng City anymore.

160
00:13:19,860 --> 00:13:21,760
Handmade rice noodles.

161
00:13:21,760 --> 00:13:23,142
Quite old-school.

162
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:27,480
It's the same flavor as the roast goose stall
on Huaihua Street back then.

163
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:28,987
Exactly the same.

164
00:13:29,845 --> 00:13:31,178
Eat up.

165
00:13:44,560 --> 00:13:46,170
What's wrong, Yi?

166
00:13:50,813 --> 00:13:52,916
It really is the taste of Huaihua Street.

167
00:13:57,266 --> 00:13:59,336
Why have you been absent so much lately?

168
00:14:04,160 --> 00:14:05,240
Me?

169
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:07,040
My old stomach trouble.

170
00:14:07,040 --> 00:14:08,896
I've been to the hospital a few times.

171
00:14:10,073 --> 00:14:12,861
Look. I even forgot to take my medicine today.

172
00:14:14,267 --> 00:14:15,720
I'll go get it.

173
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:17,500
- You eat first.
- Wait.

174
00:14:17,500 --> 00:14:19,597
Where is the medicine? I'll get it for you.

175
00:14:21,413 --> 00:14:25,017
It's in my cab, in that red bag.

176
00:14:25,017 --> 00:14:27,103
Okay. Wait here.

177
00:14:27,103 --> 00:14:28,585
Thank you, Yi.

178
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:41,980
Here.

179
00:14:41,980 --> 00:14:43,399
Thank you, Yi.

180
00:14:44,620 --> 00:14:47,962
Haven't I made enough runs this month?

181
00:14:48,739 --> 00:14:49,765
No.

182
00:14:49,765 --> 00:14:52,420
It's just some new drivers.
They don't know the rules.

183
00:14:52,420 --> 00:14:54,260
One of them loaded cargo from Baiyou No. Four.

184
00:14:54,260 --> 00:14:56,160
He almost made a mistake.

185
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:58,800
That small cargo isn't ours.

186
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:01,679
We always deliver to the docks.
We only deliver the No. Seven cargo.

187
00:15:01,679 --> 00:15:04,483
The other numbers...
those are all for the large trucks.

188
00:15:18,080 --> 00:15:19,517
Seven?

189
00:15:20,700 --> 00:15:21,926
It's this kind?

190
00:15:24,433 --> 00:15:27,350
Yi. I didn't steal this.

191
00:15:28,020 --> 00:15:31,000
It fell out from under the pallet.

192
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:34,086
I only found it when I was finishing my shift.

193
00:15:35,446 --> 00:15:38,627
I saw it wasn't dirty or torn,

194
00:15:39,420 --> 00:15:42,168
so I wanted to take it home for my daughter.

195
00:15:46,380 --> 00:15:48,268
Where's the medicine?

196
00:15:59,345 --> 00:16:01,871
It's all gone. I forgot to get a refill.

197
00:16:03,566 --> 00:16:07,131
Yi, I'll try to make more trips next month.

198
00:16:07,131 --> 00:16:09,007
I didn't say I was firing you.

199
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:12,779
The seal is broken on this.
I'll report it as damaged later.

200
00:16:12,779 --> 00:16:14,592
Thank you, Yi.

201
00:16:15,280 --> 00:16:17,139
When did you get stomach problems?

202
00:16:17,139 --> 00:16:18,841
You were fine before.

203
00:16:19,700 --> 00:16:21,680
It's been three or four months.

204
00:16:21,680 --> 00:16:26,146
And I have diabetes,
so I don't dare eat just anything.

205
00:16:29,059 --> 00:16:33,071
Besides you,
is anyone else in the fleet feeling unwell?

206
00:16:41,940 --> 00:16:43,710
It's nothing much, really.

207
00:16:44,620 --> 00:16:50,220
At most,
everyone has headaches and a loss of appetite.

208
00:16:50,220 --> 00:16:53,379
Because lately,
everyone's been working night shifts.

209
00:16:53,379 --> 00:16:57,201
Basically, everyone is the same.

210
00:17:11,186 --> 00:17:13,137
Let's get you to the hospital first.

211
00:17:17,360 --> 00:17:19,230
Bai Guo Qiang, right?

212
00:17:19,230 --> 00:17:22,600
This is your bed. This is your hospital gown.

213
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:25,040
You can go ahead and get changed now.

214
00:17:25,040 --> 00:17:26,519
There's a call bell next to the bed.

215
00:17:26,519 --> 00:17:29,359
If you need anything, you can call us anytime.

216
00:17:29,359 --> 00:17:31,451
Okay. Thank you, miss.

217
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:36,152
Have you contacted your family?

218
00:17:37,460 --> 00:17:39,619
My daughter is only in elementary school.

219
00:17:39,619 --> 00:17:41,180
Someone has to be home to mind her.

220
00:17:41,180 --> 00:17:43,000
My wife has an early shift tomorrow.

221
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:45,120
It's just a bit of indigestion.

222
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:47,715
I don't really need to be hospitalized.

223
00:18:00,927 --> 00:18:02,682
What's this on your back?

224
00:18:05,220 --> 00:18:07,019
It's just some rashes.

225
00:18:07,019 --> 00:18:08,859
I've been applying safflower oil.

226
00:18:08,859 --> 00:18:11,149
It's been over two weeks,
but it hasn't gotten any better.

227
00:18:12,199 --> 00:18:15,371
Since it didn't go away,
why didn't you come to the hospital?

228
00:18:17,119 --> 00:18:21,339
Driving day and night,
we eat and sleep in the truck.

229
00:18:21,339 --> 00:18:23,420
Where would I find the time?

230
00:18:24,380 --> 00:18:26,814
I'll go check the results with the doctor.

231
00:18:42,700 --> 00:18:45,720
Your company is in the transport business.

232
00:18:45,720 --> 00:18:49,148
And you're hauling hazardous goods.
Why weren't there safety precautions?

233
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:51,610
Here, take a look.

234
00:18:52,245 --> 00:18:56,888
White blood cells, platelets...
None of the counts is normal.

235
00:19:03,759 --> 00:19:05,620
What's the exact situation?

236
00:19:05,620 --> 00:19:08,080
He already has diabetes.

237
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:12,910
Judging by the severity,
he's been exposed for at least a month.

238
00:19:12,910 --> 00:19:14,480
Are you sure that's the cause?

239
00:19:14,480 --> 00:19:17,433
The others in the fleet
don't seem to have much of a reaction.

240
00:19:18,059 --> 00:19:19,259
Let me put it this way.

241
00:19:19,259 --> 00:19:23,240
This patient already has
a low white blood cell count.

242
00:19:23,240 --> 00:19:28,380
Even if everyone else is fine,
he would be the first to fall ill.

243
00:19:28,380 --> 00:19:31,899
This can't be delayed any longer.
He must be hospitalized immediately.

244
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:35,700
What exactly does your company transport?

245
00:19:35,700 --> 00:19:37,570
Don't you know?

246
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:23,187
Can you tell what this is?

247
00:20:25,740 --> 00:20:27,710
Silver-gray,

248
00:20:28,539 --> 00:20:32,393
with a metallic luster, and denser than iron.

249
00:20:33,020 --> 00:20:37,263
If I'm not mistaken,
this should be germanium metal.

250
00:20:41,880 --> 00:20:44,940
These people have some nerve.

251
00:20:47,619 --> 00:20:49,747
Can we open a case with this?

252
00:20:50,660 --> 00:20:54,360
Evidence obtained through illegal means
can't be used to open a case.

253
00:20:54,360 --> 00:20:55,580
Yeah.

254
00:20:55,580 --> 00:20:57,640
It would compromise judicial fairness.

255
00:20:57,640 --> 00:20:59,700
It can't be used as a basis for a case.

256
00:20:59,700 --> 00:21:01,255
That's a pity.

257
00:21:02,445 --> 00:21:06,550
I'll take it back to the station.
The forensics will examine it thoroughly.

258
00:21:07,240 --> 00:21:11,754
Look on the bright side. At least now,
we're not just talking without proof.

259
00:21:12,539 --> 00:21:16,504
What we're missing now
is just one official chance to make an arrest.

260
00:21:21,140 --> 00:21:22,667
It'll be soon.

261
00:21:29,700 --> 00:21:31,220
Dry my hair.

262
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:44,773
Lean forward.

263
00:22:01,032 --> 00:22:04,958
When you saw Uncle Zhou off just now,
what did he say to you?

264
00:22:06,119 --> 00:22:08,099
I updated him on the situation.

265
00:22:08,099 --> 00:22:11,440
Remember when you joined me
for the inventory check?

266
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:14,602
That's when I discovered
something was wrong with Haoyun's fleet.

267
00:22:15,480 --> 00:22:18,620
I've mostly figured out
their transport methods.

268
00:22:18,620 --> 00:22:21,820
Bai's vehicle is a small truck.

269
00:22:21,820 --> 00:22:24,860
On the rear tailgate,
the license plate isn't painted on.

270
00:22:25,519 --> 00:22:27,140
There are two teams like this.

271
00:22:27,140 --> 00:22:29,519
The vehicle models are exactly the same.

272
00:22:29,519 --> 00:22:32,586
Let's call them the black and white cars.

273
00:22:43,880 --> 00:22:46,440
Between the checkpoint and the border,
there's a stretch of road.

274
00:22:46,440 --> 00:22:50,025
This is the place
where they pull off the switch.

275
00:22:57,620 --> 00:22:59,240
The white truck enters the checkpoint.

276
00:22:59,240 --> 00:23:02,573
The black truck takes a detour
to an abandoned parking lot.

277
00:23:17,880 --> 00:23:20,660
The white truck carries no smuggled goods.

278
00:23:20,660 --> 00:23:22,689
The goods are all in the black truck.

279
00:23:24,900 --> 00:23:28,580
[Motor Vehicle Inspection Card Stub]
So the white truck passes the checkpoint safely

280
00:23:28,580 --> 00:23:30,729
and leaves a clean record.

281
00:23:31,453 --> 00:23:33,777
They swap license plates there.

282
00:23:33,777 --> 00:23:35,602
So when they emerge,

283
00:23:35,602 --> 00:23:38,651
the black truck is already
using the white truck's plates.

284
00:23:46,120 --> 00:23:49,300
Those stuffed toys
are their means of transport.

285
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:53,820
In Lingang, I found that
they have only six official production lines.

286
00:23:53,820 --> 00:23:58,140
But plushies with a serial number starting
with seven don't exist on the market.

287
00:23:58,140 --> 00:24:01,160
They only circulate
within Haoyun's transport routes.

288
00:24:01,160 --> 00:24:04,168
That's how they smuggle the goods.

289
00:24:09,160 --> 00:24:11,680
Don't frown like Uncle Zhou.

290
00:24:11,680 --> 00:24:14,272
Don't worry. They have a plan.

291
00:24:15,100 --> 00:24:19,772
Since you've handed it over to the police,
don't get involved anymore.

292
00:24:22,440 --> 00:24:25,822
No more playing the hero. Got it?

293
00:24:42,900 --> 00:24:44,956
Lights off. Time for bed.

294
00:24:46,280 --> 00:24:48,662
You're quite used to lying here.

295
00:24:50,333 --> 00:24:52,220
It's not like I haven't before.

296
00:24:52,220 --> 00:24:55,860
A few days ago, when my sheets weren't dry,
I slept right here.

297
00:24:58,599 --> 00:25:00,327
Hurry up.

298
00:25:22,373 --> 00:25:25,119
Let me tell you,
when I went to Lingang a few days ago,

299
00:25:25,119 --> 00:25:28,480
I visited so many malls.
Cen Ye and I went to every single one.

300
00:25:28,480 --> 00:25:30,569
We were looking for that...

301
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:44,053
Just go to sleep.

302
00:26:03,559 --> 00:26:04,923
Sleep.

303
00:26:22,260 --> 00:26:25,880
Bai is sick. Who's leading the team this time?

304
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:27,380
Who knows?

305
00:26:27,380 --> 00:26:30,158
They haven't said a word.
They just have us waiting.

306
00:26:32,340 --> 00:26:34,279
Why don't you go ask?

307
00:26:34,279 --> 00:26:37,514
- Go ask.
- Go on.

308
00:26:42,319 --> 00:26:43,720
Mr. Tao.

309
00:26:43,720 --> 00:26:46,180
- Manager, when are we leaving?
- Yes?

310
00:26:46,180 --> 00:26:48,468
What are we hauling this time?

311
00:26:50,559 --> 00:26:51,880
Just wait.

312
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:54,020
Don't ask questions.
Just drive the route as usual.

313
00:26:54,020 --> 00:26:56,440
Don't delay the job. Off you go.

314
00:26:56,440 --> 00:26:58,077
Yes.

315
00:27:14,759 --> 00:27:16,380
Tired of waiting?

316
00:27:19,433 --> 00:27:20,934
Waiting for nothing.

317
00:27:23,380 --> 00:27:24,984
Who's that?

318
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:32,069
Let's move out.

319
00:27:33,599 --> 00:27:35,594
Is that the new guy?

320
00:27:36,380 --> 00:27:38,920
He's acting so high and mighty.

321
00:27:38,920 --> 00:27:41,039
Alright. Stop staring. Let's go.

322
00:27:41,039 --> 00:27:43,949
Alright, let's go.

323
00:28:43,519 --> 00:28:45,760
Get out of the truck. Routine inspection.

324
00:28:45,760 --> 00:28:47,448
Open the trunk.

325
00:28:49,019 --> 00:28:53,871
It's just some toys.

326
00:28:53,871 --> 00:28:55,530
Nothing else.

327
00:28:56,706 --> 00:28:59,600
Please show your vehicle registration
and driver's license.

328
00:28:59,600 --> 00:29:03,099
The documents are in my truck. Follow me.

329
00:29:15,785 --> 00:29:16,953
Officer.

330
00:29:16,953 --> 00:29:20,538
This is my shipping manifest.

331
00:29:21,265 --> 00:29:22,873
Driver's license.

332
00:29:23,680 --> 00:29:25,180
Vehicle registration.

333
00:29:25,180 --> 00:29:27,240
ID card.

334
00:29:27,240 --> 00:29:29,420
[Sun Hu]

335
00:29:31,146 --> 00:29:32,940
You're a driver for Haoyun.

336
00:29:32,940 --> 00:29:34,080
That's right.

337
00:29:34,080 --> 00:29:35,556
It's me.

338
00:29:38,739 --> 00:29:41,881
Stop! Stop right there!

339
00:29:44,619 --> 00:29:47,099
It has nothing to do with me! Take it easy!

340
00:29:47,099 --> 00:29:48,487
Why are you running?

341
00:29:49,980 --> 00:29:52,640
Officer Zhou, we're all old friends.

342
00:29:52,640 --> 00:29:53,988
It's you.

343
00:29:54,720 --> 00:29:56,999
I just didn't bring my ID today.

344
00:29:56,999 --> 00:29:58,339
- What's in the truck?
- We've checked it.

345
00:29:58,339 --> 00:30:00,660
The truck is full of plushies. Nothing else.

346
00:30:02,640 --> 00:30:05,180
- Take him and the truck back.
- Yes, sir.

347
00:30:05,180 --> 00:30:08,000
Officer Zhou,
I'll get a replacement tomorrow. Is that okay?

348
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:09,559
Take him away.

349
00:30:13,986 --> 00:30:16,539
Officer Zhou is my friend!

350
00:30:16,539 --> 00:30:19,380
I didn't do it!

351
00:30:19,380 --> 00:30:22,279
Officer, I've been here so many times.

352
00:30:22,279 --> 00:30:23,920
Chen Yi.

353
00:30:23,920 --> 00:30:25,420
- What are you doing?
- What do you think you're doing?

354
00:30:25,420 --> 00:30:27,725
- Don't move.
- Behave yourself.

355
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:30,980
Mr. Zhai must have been blind.

356
00:30:30,980 --> 00:30:33,632
He got Zhang Bin a good lapdog.

357
00:30:36,433 --> 00:30:38,557
What's going on? Behave yourself.

358
00:30:38,557 --> 00:30:40,359
- Take him inside.
- I didn't do anything wrong!

359
00:30:40,359 --> 00:30:41,687
Get in!

360
00:30:43,906 --> 00:30:45,120
It's fine.

361
00:30:45,812 --> 00:30:50,558
You two have been going back and forth
between the hospital and the police station.

362
00:30:50,558 --> 00:30:53,168
Go home and get some pomelo leaves
to wash away the bad luck.

363
00:30:53,912 --> 00:30:55,574
Again?

364
00:30:56,359 --> 00:30:57,724
Just listen to me.

365
00:30:57,724 --> 00:30:59,204
This way.

366
00:31:04,285 --> 00:31:05,718
Careful.

367
00:31:16,819 --> 00:31:20,680
Although Zhang Bin has no direct connection
to Sun Hu's case,

368
00:31:20,680 --> 00:31:23,975
you still need to be careful.

369
00:31:51,380 --> 00:31:54,302
Officer Zhou,
I've caused you a lot of trouble lately.

370
00:31:54,302 --> 00:31:55,416
Thank you.

371
00:31:56,065 --> 00:31:57,291
It's my duty.

372
00:31:57,291 --> 00:31:58,967
Don't mention it.

373
00:32:04,560 --> 00:32:06,091
Are you all right?

374
00:32:11,520 --> 00:32:16,868
This whole ordeal has been quite a shock
for Yi and his sister.

375
00:32:17,780 --> 00:32:19,600
I've found a place.

376
00:32:19,600 --> 00:32:23,330
I'll take them to play pool to unwind.

377
00:32:24,400 --> 00:32:27,323
If you're interested, why not join us?

378
00:32:28,099 --> 00:32:30,720
No, thanks. I'm on duty.

379
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:32,347
I'm a bit occupied.

380
00:32:33,306 --> 00:32:34,780
I won't insist then.

381
00:32:36,055 --> 00:32:40,170
By the way,
public safety hasn't been great lately.

382
00:32:40,170 --> 00:32:43,515
I have a word of advice for you.
Keep a low profile.

383
00:32:43,515 --> 00:32:45,460
Watch your step at night.

384
00:32:45,460 --> 00:32:46,880
Don't worry.

385
00:32:46,880 --> 00:32:49,622
I certainly won't cause the police any trouble.

386
00:32:53,319 --> 00:32:54,799
Let's go.

387
00:32:54,799 --> 00:32:56,887
You two, sit in the back.

388
00:32:59,340 --> 00:33:00,860
What are you waiting for?

389
00:33:00,860 --> 00:33:03,854
I'm asking you to sit in the back
so it's easier for us to talk.

390
00:33:06,180 --> 00:33:07,740
Li.

391
00:33:50,740 --> 00:33:54,147
I'll go and reapply for that ID tomorrow.
Is that okay?

392
00:33:54,147 --> 00:33:55,340
Officer Zhou.

393
00:33:55,340 --> 00:33:56,579
Step outside for a moment. Let me handle this.

394
00:33:56,579 --> 00:33:58,962
I didn't do anything wrong.

395
00:34:09,887 --> 00:34:11,800
Tell me about the arson.

396
00:34:11,800 --> 00:34:13,805
Confess, and we'll go easy on you.

397
00:34:13,805 --> 00:34:15,590
Maybe you'll get a few years off.

398
00:34:15,590 --> 00:34:17,712
[Surveillance footage showing Sun Hu nearby.
Footage showing Sun Hu committing the crime.]

399
00:34:24,300 --> 00:34:25,863
I'll talk.

400
00:34:29,380 --> 00:34:33,100
Officer Zhou has been promoted quickly
over the past few years.

401
00:34:33,100 --> 00:34:35,380
He's capable and dedicated.

402
00:34:35,380 --> 00:34:39,008
He won't have to worry
about his future in the force.

403
00:34:41,260 --> 00:34:46,266
But I heard that he's still single.

404
00:34:48,960 --> 00:34:54,372
The clerk who died in that fire years ago

405
00:34:55,746 --> 00:34:58,195
was apparently his fiancée.

406
00:35:01,112 --> 00:35:02,540
What a pity.

407
00:35:04,440 --> 00:35:07,991
The wicked prosper while the good suffer.
It is a pity indeed.

408
00:35:13,539 --> 00:35:15,559
So what if they prosper for a while?

409
00:35:15,559 --> 00:35:19,711
Once they're wanted,
they're just rats scurrying across the street.

410
00:35:25,500 --> 00:35:27,400
Let me introduce you.

411
00:35:27,400 --> 00:35:28,740
This is Coach Hu.

412
00:35:28,740 --> 00:35:31,100
Yi. You should remember her.

413
00:35:31,100 --> 00:35:33,189
You played against her back in the 2000s.

414
00:35:48,793 --> 00:35:49,996
I remember.

415
00:35:50,840 --> 00:35:52,060
Today,

416
00:35:52,060 --> 00:35:55,760
I just want the two of you
to come here and relax.

417
00:35:55,760 --> 00:35:59,602
Since there are four of us,
let's play American pool.

418
00:36:02,953 --> 00:36:04,645
Do you know how to play?

419
00:36:18,920 --> 00:36:21,940
Chen Yi, you took the heat for me this time.

420
00:36:21,940 --> 00:36:25,820
Regarding Sun Hu, you two helped me a lot.

421
00:36:25,820 --> 00:36:27,260
Thank you.

422
00:36:30,080 --> 00:36:33,074
His target was always me.

423
00:36:34,560 --> 00:36:37,871
He's probably still bitter about
what happened to Mr. Zhai back then.

424
00:36:39,880 --> 00:36:43,029
You've shown him enough respect.

425
00:36:46,340 --> 00:36:49,500
Mr. Zhang, you were so focused
on the new routes before.

426
00:36:49,500 --> 00:36:54,080
Now that Sun Hu has messed things up,
you must have a backup plan.

427
00:36:54,080 --> 00:36:55,619
Do I?

428
00:36:58,140 --> 00:37:00,840
Those routes are being monitored
more closely by police.

429
00:37:00,840 --> 00:37:03,340
Many procedures need to be redone.

430
00:37:03,340 --> 00:37:06,202
But the customers' goods cannot be delayed.

431
00:37:06,920 --> 00:37:10,400
As for other ways...

432
00:37:10,400 --> 00:37:14,346
As for other ways, it depends on your brother.

433
00:37:15,539 --> 00:37:18,659
Just like the arson last time.

434
00:37:18,659 --> 00:37:20,700
It was thrilling,

435
00:37:20,700 --> 00:37:22,719
but compared to
what he experienced in Country Jin,

436
00:37:22,719 --> 00:37:25,079
that was nothing.

437
00:37:26,466 --> 00:37:28,000
Country Jin?

438
00:37:28,000 --> 00:37:29,560
You've been to Country Jin?

439
00:37:29,560 --> 00:37:31,779
Mr. Zhang, you made the shot!

440
00:37:33,180 --> 00:37:34,876
I forgot.

441
00:37:56,893 --> 00:37:58,366
The eight ball went in.

442
00:38:01,180 --> 00:38:03,660
I was just focused on the eight ball.

443
00:38:03,660 --> 00:38:07,416
Chen Yi, you're not on your game today.

444
00:38:08,200 --> 00:38:09,720
Let's play another round.

445
00:38:09,720 --> 00:38:13,654
I'd better not. We have other things to do.
We'll be going now.

446
00:38:15,920 --> 00:38:18,360
Mr. Zhang, I'll be going, too.

447
00:38:18,360 --> 00:38:19,699
Okay.

448
00:38:20,520 --> 00:38:22,598
I'll have Li give you a ride.

449
00:38:29,780 --> 00:38:32,320
A few years ago, he'd just turned 18.

450
00:38:32,320 --> 00:38:35,951
A mere kid made me lose face completely.

451
00:38:36,680 --> 00:38:39,529
I never thought
the day would come to get my win back.

452
00:38:40,807 --> 00:38:43,771
Do you know why he lost today?

453
00:38:45,660 --> 00:38:50,060
He let his guard down and got rusty?

454
00:38:50,060 --> 00:38:54,249
After all,
he doesn't need to gamble to survive now.

455
00:38:58,720 --> 00:39:03,739
Back then, he was poor.
He had no money, and his life was cheap.

456
00:39:03,739 --> 00:39:05,680
So he wasn't afraid of anything.

457
00:39:05,680 --> 00:39:08,060
But it's different now.

458
00:39:08,060 --> 00:39:11,623
Now he has things he values
and people he cares about.

459
00:39:12,980 --> 00:39:15,933
So he can't be completely focused.

460
00:39:17,820 --> 00:39:19,920
You know how it is.

461
00:39:19,920 --> 00:39:23,500
When a player steps up to the table,

462
00:39:23,500 --> 00:39:27,500
he has to be absolutely clear
about the position he wants

463
00:39:27,500 --> 00:39:30,931
and the pocket he's playing for on every shot.

464
00:39:33,440 --> 00:39:34,843
So,

465
00:39:35,780 --> 00:39:38,818
if you want to clear your mind,

466
00:39:43,020 --> 00:39:45,016
you still have work to do.

467
00:39:54,659 --> 00:39:57,400
Why didn't you tell me
about your time in Country Jin?

468
00:39:57,400 --> 00:39:59,713
Chen Yi, what else are you hiding from me?

469
00:40:00,500 --> 00:40:02,921
Can't you just be honest?

470
00:40:04,273 --> 00:40:07,153
- Miao Jing.
- I don't want to talk to you.

471
00:40:48,618 --> 00:40:50,732
Why are you back so late?

472
00:41:00,673 --> 00:41:04,617
You're quite obedient,
doing whatever Zhou Kang An says.

473
00:41:04,617 --> 00:41:06,121
Stand still.

474
00:41:09,253 --> 00:41:11,199
It's good to wash away the bad luck.

475
00:41:11,199 --> 00:41:14,311
Perhaps I'll have to
go see him a few more times.

476
00:41:15,880 --> 00:41:18,560
I'm not necessarily the one he wants to see.

477
00:41:18,560 --> 00:41:20,479
I hope not.

478
00:41:22,867 --> 00:41:26,695
If you want to wade into these murky waters,
I can't stop you.

479
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:35,020
I can stir up the waters,
but I can also make them clear.

480
00:41:39,140 --> 00:41:40,626
Do you trust me?

481
00:41:42,840 --> 00:41:44,273
I trust you.

482
00:41:46,920 --> 00:41:49,246
But we both have to make it out alive.

483
00:41:51,960 --> 00:41:57,300
If you're going to risk your life,
you'd better do a risk assessment first.

484
00:42:04,399 --> 00:42:05,820
Don't hit my head.

485
00:42:05,820 --> 00:42:08,622
- What?
- I said, don't hit my head.

486
00:42:14,540 --> 00:42:18,080
[Haoyun Logistics]

487
00:43:52,179 --> 00:43:53,579
- What's going on?
- I haven't saved my work yet!

488
00:43:53,579 --> 00:43:54,960
- I didn't save mine either!
- What do we do?

489
00:43:54,960 --> 00:43:56,528
- Was all that work for nothing?
- That's strange.

490
00:43:56,528 --> 00:43:58,067
I'm supposed to hand in this form.

491
00:43:58,067 --> 00:44:00,824
Do you think we're cursed this year?

492
00:44:02,579 --> 00:44:05,852
Your zodiac year was years ago!
Forget about bad luck.

493
00:44:06,840 --> 00:44:11,974
In Teng City, we say, "Go with the flow."
Just think of it as a paid break.

